  "prompt": "What is the minimum marks needed to get mechanical branch in BITS Pilani?",
  "response": "The minimum marks required to secure admission to the mechanical engineering branch at BITS Pilani can vary each year based on a variety of factors such as the difficulty of the entrance examination (BITSAT), the number of applicants, and the overall performance of the candidates. Historically, the cutoff scores for mechanical engineering at BITS Pilani have been around 300-330 marks in BITSAT.\n\nHowever, these numbers can change annually, so it is advisable to check the latest information directly from the official BITS Pilani admission website or contact the admissions office to get the most current and accurate cutoff details.",
